Saturday I plan to try again. The weather doesn't look good now, but today is Monday.
It seems that the challenges in this area are starting to show. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I might have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and involve a lot of extra work.
Although this is somewhat frustrating, it's just another problem to solve, and it seems "definitely" solvable for now. The only issue is that it will take a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'm facing next:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
