#TeaganAir
Flight log book has officially been activated. I have 2.3 hours of flight records now ^_^
#TeaganAir
If I were to describe what it's like to fly a small plane, I would say it's like driving a motorcycle/ATV and boat hybrid at 4000 feet in the air.
On the ground, things change in an instant. There is a certain degree of instability on the ground, so a motorcycle/ATV is needed.
Additionally, you might not know that when flying on the ground, you control the direction with your feet, not with the control stick. You use the rudder pedals and brakes. It's not like driving a car.
When flying in the air, you will feel turbulence and shaking, which feels like being on a boat on the water. Although you can control the plane, sometimes the airflow can make you feel dizzy and disoriented, so you need to adapt to flying in the air, just like a sailor adapts to sailing.
There's also a random little tidbit about this:
Flying is very physically demanding. My back and legs are really sore today, feeling like I went to the gym.
This isn't as simple as a Sunday drive. In my view, as a beginner, it feels more like a sport than a cruise.
Dear friends, happy Saturday. Welcome to 4000 feet in the air.
Tomorrow I will fly again, and we will practice stalls and slow flight.
Today's weather was a bit unstable, but super fun. We practiced slow flight and stalls. Our ground speed dropped as low as 16 miles per hour, while our airspeed was still at 65 miles per hour.
Today was sunny, and although there was some mist at high altitude, the visibility was still great.
